Effect Size Estimation Bias for groupedSurv and Coxph Box plot comparing bias of effect size estimation of groupedSurv and Coxph

Having established control of type I error, the simulation results for the power estimations for the grouped failure time method are shown in Fig. 3 for MAFs of 0.05, 0.1, 0.2 and 0.5. An event rate of 0.6 and a sample size of n=1000 is used for each example, with the effect size varying over the range of β∈(−0.9,0.9). Power is estimated at the two-sided α=0.05 level using B=10,000 replicates.
